{"TopicId":221489,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Remove Symmetry Mystery!","CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T18:35:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T18:35:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been playing Kerbal Space Program for 10 years now.\u00A0 I am so excited about the new science update and started playing KSP2 again.\u00A0 But for the life of me I couldn\u0027t figure out how to remove symmetry from a pair of antennas.\u00A0 So I googled it.\u00A0 It turns out you have to press\u003Cstrong\u003E left alt, left shift and then left click\u003C/strong\u003E to remove the symmetry.\u00A0 Please tell me there is an easier way?\u00A0 Maybe I missed it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCome on now, that\u0027s like knowing how to press ctrl-alt-del the first time you set down to a computer.\u00A0 We need a button or option to do this that only takes a one or two mouse clicks.\u00A0 I\u0027m way too lazy to press buttons on the keyboard.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T21:07:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved to suggestions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sea_Kerman","CreatedById":226149,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T23:04:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat doesn\u0027t appear to do anything\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T13:19:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224349473\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221489\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703113496\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226149\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sea_Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Sea_Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat doesn\u0027t appear to do anything\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to use it on a part that already has symmetry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sea_Kerman","CreatedById":226149,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T17:53:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:16:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery strange. It worked for me.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"P4ntik","CreatedById":233178,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-02T12:22:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo shortcuts work for me.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI managed to remove parts from symetry by clicking middle mouse button in the stage part. Even after removing from symetry it\u0027s so tricky...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-04-02T12:46:59Z\u0022 title=\u002204/02/2024 12:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Apr 2\u0022\u003EApril 2\u003C/time\u003E by P4ntik\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}